HEADWORD: Water-closet
<hw>Wa"ter-clos`et</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A privy;
especially, a privy furnished with a contrivance for introducing a
stream of water to cleanse it.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

